    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Aim of the current study is to test the non-inferiority hypothesis of differences in early
      hip dislocation between a group of patients who will be restricted to sleep in supine
      position and a group without restricted sleeping position during the first eight weeks after
      a total hip replacement following a posterolateral surgical approach
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      stratified block randomized controlled trial
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
