  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Placement of a primary total hip replacement via the posterolateral approach by a high
             volume orthopaedic surgeon

          -  Patients with a ASA-classification of I or II

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Blindness

          -  Replacement of 2nd total hip within six months after the1st total hip replacement
             surgery

          -  Insufficient knowledge of the Dutch language

          -  Collum fracture

          -  Infection of total hip replacement

          -  Cognitive dysfunction

          -  Wheelchair dependability

          -  Hypermobility

          -  Alcohol abuse

          -  Neurological disorders such as Parkinson and stroke
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
